reviews.text: Chinese restaurant, great value and nice food, suitable for a bigger group of people as the portion of the food is quite big

Awesome food in a very local setting. You’ll have to be able to look past the environment and class for patrons (sometimes smoke) to enjoy this. 

Lots of signature Cantonese beer buddies (deep fried squid & assorted items), amazing selection of local cuisine as well as hot pot for winter.
Westerners simply must understand they will not find western hygiene standards in different parts of the world.  I look past that and enjoy the atmosphere and the food.
Fair
Delicious but a bit unhygienic, still a really nice place to try Hong Kong style cuisine.
